logic.simulator
Class PokerHandSimulatorVersion2

java.lang.Object
  logic.simulator.AbstractPokerHandSimulator
      logic.simulator.PokerHandSimulatorVersion2

public class PokerHandSimulatorVersion2
extends AbstractPokerHandSimulator

Better implementation of AbstractPokerHandSimulator. This simulator only finds the best hand from the list of all possible hands. It doesn't sort all the hands.

PokerHandSimulatorVersion2

public PokerHandSimulatorVersion2(java.util.List<AbstractStartingHand> startingHands,
                                  int numberOfSimulations)
Creates a new hand simulator without any board cards. The board will be used in the simulation if the given starting hands have a game type with uses community cards.

Parameters:
startingHands - List of starting hands
numberOfSimulations - Number of simulations.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if numberOfSimulations isn't positive
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if there are less than two startingHands.
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if hands or the board have overlapping cards, or if some of the starting hands aren't full.
